(427, 1, '2018-05-27 16:42:27', '2018-05-27 11:12:27', 'The United Nations Department of Political Affairs is the department of the Secretariat of the United Nations with the role of observing, assessing and analyzing the global political developments and then advising the UN Secretary General and his envoys to assist in the peaceful prevention and resolution of conflicts around the world. Established in 1992, the Department primarily addresses five issues which includes: Prevention and Mediation, Election, Decolonization, Palestinian Rights, Secretariat Support to Security Council and women, peace and security. On the basis of the issue taken up and the agenda at hand, portfolios that are to be seated in the committee are to be decided.\r\n\r\n<strong>Committee level: Advanced</strong>\r\n<strong> Committee strength: 40 (Single Delegate)</strong>', 'The United Nations Department of Political Affairs (UNDPA)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-united-nations-department-of-political-affairs-undpa', '', '', '2018-05-27 17:01:26', '2018-05-27 11:31:26', '', 0, 'http://localhost/KiitMun18/?post_type=committee&#038;p=427', 0, 'committee', '', 0),
