(449, 1, '2018-05-27 17:01:35', '2018-05-27 11:31:35', 'The International Law Commission was established by the United Nations General Assembly in 1948 for global promotion, development and proper codification of international law. The ILC was created in order to ensure maintenance of international peace and security by ensuring that all nations abide by and correctly interpret international law for its proper implementation, directed towards conflictprevention and resolution. The Commission has 34 members with all professional experts in the field of international law, elected by the General Assembly from a list of members nominated by the governments of the member states. The primary work of the ILC is flawlessly regulated and governed by its statute, initially approved by the General Assembly of the UN.\n\n<strong>Committee level: Advanced</strong>\n<strong> Committee strength: 40 (Single Delegate)</strong>', 'The International Law Commission (ILC)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '424-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-05-27 17:01:35', '2018-05-27 11:31:35', '', 424, 'http://localhost/KiitMun18/424-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
