(461, 1, '2018-05-27 17:05:27', '2018-05-27 11:35:27', 'The International Organization for Migration is an intergovernmental organization that provides recommendations concerning to migration, including internally and externally displaced persons, refugees, and migrant workers. IOM was established in 1951 to help resettle people displaced by World War II. The IOM has its own constitution. The IOM constitution lays out detailed analysis on the relationship between migration and social, economic and cultural development and also to the right of freedom of movement of persons. IOM basically works in four major areas of migration management which includes: Migration and Development, Facilitating Migration, Addressing Forced Migration and Regulating Migration. IOM has 166 member states and eight observer states.\n\n<strong>Committee level: Beginner</strong>\n<strong> Committee strength: 140 (Single Delegate)</strong>', 'International Organization for Migration (IOM)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '288-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-05-27 17:05:27', '2018-05-27 11:35:27', '', 288, 'http://localhost/KiitMun18/288-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
